We think democracy is the best. Yeah it is at this time, but just because we cannot imagine it we can create a better System. One that doesnt exist yet. Everyone is saying it's impossible.. i say no... everything is possible .
The meaning of believing in utopia is not to unrealistic. You need unrealistic Visions of future and a maybe dream utopia. Cause when we dont start to believe that there can be a better World we will not take the steps that are needed. title: 2539 • Ua1XhwLeXqdj
name: John Paul Readey
text:
I want the future to remember that not everything in life is horrible, nor is everyone horrible. There are beautiful things and people in life, and life is worth living. If you ever feel like there is no more time left, please reach out to someone, you matter to more people than you believe. Even if you dont feel like it. People would rather see you and hear your voice, than attend your funeral. 

Quiero que el futuro recuerde que no todo en la vida es horrible, ni todos lo son.  Hay cosas y personas hermosas en la vida, y vale la pena vivirla.  Si alguna vez sientes que no queda más tiempo, comunícate con alguien, le importas a más personas de las que crees.  Incluso si no te apetece.  La gente preferiría verte y escuchar tu voz que asistir a tu funeral.

title: 2880 • TtxwmfOeIuVB
name: Alexander Sust
text: As humans we are part of nature. Our bodies are adapted to the conditions that have existed in our habitats for thousands of years. We have changed the natural habitats through our cultures. One motivation for this was to live as long and healthily as individuals as possible. Our bodies are not always optimally adapted to these changes. So we live in a culture that in some ways does not do justice to our physicality. This includes, for example, our reproduction, which is designed to produce many viable offspring. However, due to the changes in our habitats, many more people survive than are necessary to preserve the species. Our sexuality, as part of our physicality, is not adapted to these changed living conditions. We have responded to this culturally by lowering our fertility. This leads to us suppressing or manipulating part of our physical nature. This includes evanescence. As a result, we feel ashamed about our sexuality and our aging. However, in natural cycles, becoming has the same weight as passing away. I hope that in the future we will have developed a culture that celebrates the beauty of the balance of growth and decay.
